	   <tr><td colspan=2>From an RP standpoint, illusions shouldn't give any stats at all.  An illusion is making yourself look like something, not turning yourself into something.  Shamans, druids, and necromancers get the real nice effects because they are actually turning into a bear/wolf/tree/skeleton or whatever they happen to be turning into.  I never really understood why an illusion would grant any special effects.<br>&nbsp;<br>34th Mage of Cazic-Thule<br>Member of The Chosen Elite<br>25th Druid of The Nameless<br></td></tr>
